    "what_description": "Juniperus montana is a species of evergreen coniferous tree that belongs to the family Cupressaceae. It is native to the mountainous regions of Mexico and the southwestern United States, typically growing at high elevations. Juniperus montana is a small to medium-sized tree, usually reaching heights of 3-10 meters, with a conical shape and a straight trunk. The leaves are scale-like, 2-5 mm long, and arranged in opposite decussate whorls, while the cones are 1.5-3 cm long and purplish-black in color. The bark is grayish-brown and fibrous, peeling off in small flakes.",
