    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Juniperus montana are its diuretic effects, which help in the treatment of urinary retention and edema, due to the presence of volatile oils such as beta-pinene and alpha-pinene that enhance urine production. This plant also exhibits antioxidant activity, neutralizing free radicals that cause oxidative stress and cell damage, attributed to the flavonoids and phenolic acids present within its leaves and bark. Additionally, Juniperus montana has been found to possess antimicrobial properties, inhibiting the growth of various bacteria, fungi, and viruses, primarily due to the saponins and terpenes that disrupt microbial membranes. Furthermore, its anti-inflammatory effects help in reducing pain and inflammation associated with various conditions, attributed to the presence of sesquiterpenes and diterpenes that modulate the inflammatory response. The expectorant properties of Juniperus montana also aid in relieving respiratory issues such as bronchitis and asthma, primarily due to the volatile oils that help in loosening and expelling mucus from the respiratory tract.",
