    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Juniperus montana are sabinene, bornyl acetate, \u03b1-pinene, \u03b2-pinene, and limonene, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. Sabinene exhibits antimicrobial and antioxidant activities, while bornyl acetate has been found to have anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties. \u03b1-Pinene and \u03b2-pinene, both monoterpene hydrocarbons, have been shown to possess bronchodilatory and expectorant effects, aiding in respiratory issues such as asthma and bronchitis. Limonene, a known monoterpene, has been demonstrated to exhibit anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antitumor activities. These constituents contribute to Juniperus montana's traditional use in treating various ailments, including respiratory infections, inflammation, and certain types of cancer.",
