    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Juniperus montana are juniper berry tea, juniper berry tincture, juniper berry oil, juniper berry infusion, and juniper oil. Juniper berry tea is made by steeping the berries in hot water, often used to treat digestive issues and as a natural diuretic. Juniper berry tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the berries in a solvent, commonly used to treat respiratory issues and as an antiseptic. Juniper berry oil is obtained through steam distillation of the berries and used topically to treat skin irritations and as an antiseptic. Juniper oil, obtained through steam distillation of the plant's needles, is used to treat respiratory issues, skin irritations and as an antiseptic.",
